Jesus Christ,
what the hell time is it?

497
01:10:07,024 --> 01:10:09,982
- Who is that, honey?
- Listen good, Fredo.

498
01:10:10,093 --> 01:10:13,119
What are you callin' me here for?
l don't want to talk to you.

499
01:10:13,230 --> 01:10:15,460
Pentangeli's set up a meeting
with the Rosato brothers.

500
01:10:15,565 --> 01:10:17,897
- He's gonna go for their deal.
- Oh, God.

501
01:10:18,001 --> 01:10:20,526
- Will he come alone?
- l don't know anything.

502
01:10:20,637 --> 01:10:23,197
- You got me in deep enough already.
-Just go along.

503
01:10:23,306 --> 01:10:25,297
Everything will be all right,
Fredo.

504
01:10:25,409 --> 01:10:27,707
Pentangeli says he's
willing to make a deal.

505
01:10:27,811 --> 01:10:30,700
All we wanna know is
if he's on the level.

506
01:10:32,315 --> 01:10:35,341
You guys lied to me. l don't
want you to call me anymore.

507
01:10:35,452 --> 01:10:37,943
Your brother's not gonna
find out we talked.

508
01:10:38,021 --> 01:10:40,910
l don't know
what you're talkin' about.

509
01:10:50,901 --> 01:10:52,789
Who was that?

510
01:10:52,903 --> 01:10:54,791
Uh, wrong number.

511
01:11:02,012 --> 01:11:04,901
Frank, l got nobody here.

512
01:11:05,015 --> 01:11:06,903
- Wait in the car, Cheech.
- Frankie--

513
01:11:07,017 --> 01:11:08,905
lt's okay, Cheech.

514
01:11:16,059 --> 01:11:19,449
- What's this, Rosato?
- A lucky ''C'' note for our new deal.

515
01:11:22,899 --> 01:11:25,288
Richie.
Give us a taste, huh?

516
01:11:29,973 --> 01:11:33,932
Yeah, we're all real happy
about your decision, Frankie.

517
01:11:34,044 --> 01:11:38,469
- You're not gonna regret it.
- l don't like this ''C'' note.

518
01:11:38,582 --> 01:11:41,073
l take that as an insult.

519
01:11:41,151 --> 01:11:43,381
Michael Corleone says hello.

520
01:12:00,470 --> 01:12:03,564
Get him in!
Close the fuckin' door!

521
01:12:03,673 --> 01:12:06,062
Your friend the cop.
What the--

522
01:12:06,176 --> 01:12:08,906
Hey, Rich, it's dark in here.

523
01:12:09,012 --> 01:12:13,403
- Are you open or closed?
- l just come in to clean up.

524
01:12:16,787 --> 01:12:19,119
What's the matter?

525
01:12:19,222 --> 01:12:22,180
- ls that somethin' on the floor?
- Carmine, no, no. Not here!

526
01:12:22,292 --> 01:12:24,783
- Not here!
- Not here, Carmine! Not a cop!

527
01:12:24,861 --> 01:12:26,749
What?

528
01:12:26,863 --> 01:12:30,321
You open your fuckin' mouth,
l'll blow your head off!

529
01:13:16,313 --> 01:13:18,201
Freddie. Good to see ya.

530
01:13:21,117 --> 01:13:23,005
Where is he?

531
01:13:23,119 --> 01:13:25,781
He's okay. He's in the back.

532
01:13:29,793 --> 01:13:32,182
Come on, girls.
Take a hike, huh?

533
01:13:35,298 --> 01:13:37,186
ln this room here.

534
01:13:40,070 --> 01:13:43,130
- l wanna talk to him alone first.
- Come on, huh?

535
01:13:52,315 --> 01:13:55,239
l thought l could
help you, Senator.

536
01:13:59,122 --> 01:14:01,386
Hagen?

537
01:14:02,225 --> 01:14:05,285
- Listen, Hagen, l did not--
- No.

538
01:14:05,395 --> 01:14:07,454
- lt's all right.
- l didn't do anything.

539
01:14:07,564 --> 01:14:09,691
lt's okay.

540
01:14:09,799 --> 01:14:12,063
You're very lucky.

541
01:14:12,168 --> 01:14:14,659
My brother Fredo
operates this place.

542
01:14:14,738 --> 01:14:17,536
He was called before anyone.

543
01:14:17,641 --> 01:14:19,370
Now, if this had happened
someplace else...

544
01:14:19,476 --> 01:14:20,534
we couldn't
have helped you.

545
01:14:24,614 --> 01:14:29,039
When l woke up
l was on the floor...

546
01:14:29,152 --> 01:14:31,040
and l don't know
how it happened.

547
01:14:31,154 --> 01:14:33,042
You can't remember?

548
01:14:36,793 --> 01:14:38,818
l passed out.

549
01:14:44,734 --> 01:14:46,622
l'll fix it.

550
01:14:46,736 --> 01:14:48,692
Okay.

551
01:14:54,878 --> 01:14:57,073
lt was just a game.

552
01:14:57,180 --> 01:14:58,579
Jesus.

553
01:15:01,351 --> 01:15:03,239
Oh.

554
01:15:08,692 --> 01:15:10,853
Jesus!Jesus!

555
01:15:15,298 --> 01:15:18,028
Jesus God.

556
01:15:18,134 --> 01:15:20,056
Oh, God.

557
01:15:22,405 --> 01:15:26,102
l don't know and l don't
understand why l can't remember.

558
01:15:26,209 --> 01:15:29,042
You don't have to remember.
Just do as l say.

559
01:15:29,145 --> 01:15:31,739
They're putting a call in
to your office.

560
01:15:31,848 --> 01:15:35,773
Explain that you'll be there
tomorrow afternoon.

561
01:15:35,885 --> 01:15:38,012
You decided to spend the night...

562
01:15:38,121 --> 01:15:42,012
at Michael Corleone's house
in Tahoe as his guest.

563
01:15:42,726 --> 01:15:45,615
l do remember
that she was laughing.

564
01:15:47,597 --> 01:15:49,485
We'd done it before...

565
01:15:49,599 --> 01:15:52,932
and l know that l could
not have hurt that girl.

566
01:15:54,070 --> 01:15:55,958
This girl has no family.

567
01:15:56,072 --> 01:15:58,063
Nobody knows
that she worked here.

568
01:15:58,174 --> 01:16:00,665
lt'll be as though
she never existed.

569
01:16:03,346 --> 01:16:05,735
All that's left
is our friendship.

570
01:16:21,464 --> 01:16:23,352
- Yes?
- l'm sorry, Mrs. Corleone.

571
01:16:23,466 --> 01:16:27,425
- We're not to let you through.
- l'm just going to the market.

572
01:16:27,537 --> 01:16:30,097
Well, if you'll just give us a list,
we'll pick up anything you want.

573
01:16:30,206 --> 01:16:33,437
- Whose orders are these?
- Mr. Hagen's, ma'am. He's coming.

574
01:16:33,543 --> 01:16:36,671
All right, well, l'm just gonna
have to speak to Mr. Hagen.

575
01:16:42,018 --> 01:16:45,613
l wanted to explain this, but
l had business in Carson City.

576
01:16:45,722 --> 01:16:47,747
Now, this is Michael's
request for your safety.

577
01:16:47,857 --> 01:16:50,451
- We can send out for anything.
- l see.

578
01:16:50,560 --> 01:16:52,516
l'm supposed to stay
in my house.

579
01:16:52,629 --> 01:16:55,120
No, within the compound
would be fine.

580
01:16:55,231 --> 01:16:57,495
l was going to take the children
to New England next week.

581
01:16:57,600 --> 01:17:00,831
- That's off now.
- Am l a prisoner? ls that it?

582
01:17:00,937 --> 01:17:03,428
- That's not the way we look at it.
- All right, come on, kids.

583
01:17:03,506 --> 01:17:05,394
We're going back to the house.

584
01:17:07,777 --> 01:17:09,665
Joe.

585
01:17:55,492 --> 01:17:57,187
Cuba! Cuba!

586
01:18:38,334 --> 01:18:41,258
Most respected gentlemen...

587
01:18:41,371 --> 01:18:43,532
allow me to welcome you
to the city of Havana.

588
01:18:45,675 --> 01:18:50,669
l want to thank this distinguished
group of American industrialists...

589
01:18:52,715 --> 01:18:54,603
for continuing to work
with Cuba...

590
01:18:56,386 --> 01:18:58,581
toward the greatest period
of prosperity...

591
01:19:00,223 --> 01:19:02,111
in her entire history.

592
01:19:03,626 --> 01:19:07,619
Mr. William Shaw, representing
the General Fruit Company;

593
01:19:09,532 --> 01:19:11,397
Misters Corngold and Dant...

594
01:19:11,501 --> 01:19:14,299
of United Telephone
and Telegraph Company;

595
01:19:16,573 --> 01:19:18,837
Mr. Petty,
regional vice president...

596
01:19:18,942 --> 01:19:21,331
of the Pan American
Mining Corporation;

597
01:19:24,047 --> 01:19:26,242
Mr. Robert Allen
of South American Sugar,

598
01:19:28,585 --> 01:19:30,712
Mr. Michael Corleone of Nevada...

599
01:19:32,589 --> 01:19:35,888
representing our associates in
tourism and leisure activities;

600
01:19:37,427 --> 01:19:40,316
and my old friend and associate
from Florida...

601
01:19:42,465 --> 01:19:44,626
Mr. Hyman Roth.

602
01:19:44,734 --> 01:19:46,497
l would like to take this
opportunity...

603
01:19:46,603 --> 01:19:48,468
to thank United
Telephone and Telegraph...

604
01:19:48,571 --> 01:19:50,459
for their lovely Christmas gift:

605
01:19:55,111 --> 01:19:56,999
a solid gold telephone.

606
01:19:59,749 --> 01:20:02,638
Perhaps you gentlemen would
like to take a look at it.

607
01:20:04,153 --> 01:20:05,882
- Mr. President.
- Yes?

608
01:20:05,989 --> 01:20:09,049
Perhaps you would discuss
the status of rebel activity...

609
01:20:09,158 --> 01:20:11,888
and what this can mean
to our businesses.

610
01:20:11,995 --> 01:20:13,485
- Of course.
- Very lovely.

611
01:20:13,563 --> 01:20:16,054
l want to assure you
that although the rebels...

612
01:20:16,132 --> 01:20:19,329
have mounted an impressive
campaign in Las Villas...

613
01:20:25,936 --> 01:20:28,234
my staff indicates
with assurance...

614
01:20:28,338 --> 01:20:33,230
we'll drive them out of the city
of Santa Clara before the new year.

615
01:20:35,846 --> 01:20:38,406
And l want to put you all
at ease.

616
01:20:38,515 --> 01:20:42,406
We will tolerate no guerillas
in the casinos or swimming pools.

617
01:21:01,304 --> 01:21:03,192
He say that they are
making arrest...

618
01:21:03,306 --> 01:21:06,195
and in a few minutes
he'll let us through.

619
01:21:06,743 --> 01:21:08,802
Johnny.

620
01:21:31,334 --> 01:21:34,462
Well, l hope my age
is correct.

621
01:21:34,571 --> 01:21:37,665
l'm always accurate
about my age.

622
01:21:37,774 --> 01:21:41,335
Make sure that everybody
sees the cake before we cut it.

623
01:21:45,182 --> 01:21:47,878
l'm very pleased...

624
01:21:47,984 --> 01:21:50,873
you were all able to come
from such distances...

625
01:21:50,987 --> 01:21:52,181
to be with me today.

626
01:21:54,124 --> 01:21:56,820
When a man comes
to this point in his life...

627
01:21:58,361 --> 01:22:01,785
he wants to turn over the
things he's been blessed with--

628
01:22:01,898 --> 01:22:03,889
turn them over to friends--

629
01:22:04,000 --> 01:22:08,232
as a reward
for the friends he's had...

630
01:22:08,338 --> 01:22:13,571
and to make sure that everything
goes well after he's gone.

631
01:22:13,677 --> 01:22:16,339
- Not for years.
- Hear, hear.

632
01:22:16,446 --> 01:22:20,268
The doctors would disagree,
but what do they know?

633
01:22:21,785 --> 01:22:26,813
These are wonderful things
that we've achieved in Havana...

634
01:22:26,923 --> 01:22:29,983
and there's no limit to
where we can go from here.

635
01:22:30,093 --> 01:22:34,848
This kind of government knows how
to help business, to encourage it.

636
01:22:34,965 --> 01:22:38,992
The hotels here
are bigger and swankier...

637
01:22:39,102 --> 01:22:41,730
than any of the rough joints
we've put in in Vegas.

638
01:22:41,838 --> 01:22:45,171
And we can thank our friends
in the Cuban government...

639
01:22:45,275 --> 01:22:48,267
which has put up half of the cash,
with the Teamsters...

640
01:22:48,378 --> 01:22:49,902
on a dollar-for-dollar basis;

641
01:22:50,013 --> 01:22:52,846
has relaxed restrictions
on imports.

642
01:22:52,949 --> 01:22:57,340
What l'm saying is that we have now
what we have always needed:

643
01:22:57,454 --> 01:23:00,218
real partnership
with a government.

644
01:23:00,323 --> 01:23:02,917
Smaller piece.

645
01:23:03,026 --> 01:23:05,586
You all know Michael Corleone...

646
01:23:05,695 --> 01:23:07,925
and we all remember his father.

647
01:23:08,031 --> 01:23:11,660
At the time of my retirement
or death...

648
01:23:11,768 --> 01:23:16,228
l turn over all my interest
in the Havana operation...

649
01:23:16,339 --> 01:23:17,567
to his control.

650
01:23:17,674 --> 01:23:21,735
But all of you will share.

651
01:23:21,845 --> 01:23:25,542
The Nacionale will go to
the Lakeville Road boys.

652
01:23:25,649 --> 01:23:31,508
The Capri to the Corleone family.
The Sevilla Biltmore also.

653
01:23:31,621 --> 01:23:35,478
But Eddie Levine of Newport will
bring in the Pennino brothers...

654
01:23:35,592 --> 01:23:37,355
Dino and Eddie, for a piece...

655
01:23:37,460 --> 01:23:40,293
and also to handle
the actual casino operations.

656
01:23:40,397 --> 01:23:43,924
And we've saved a piece for
some friends in Nevada...

657
01:23:44,034 --> 01:23:47,697
to make sure that things
go smooth back home.

658
01:23:47,804 --> 01:23:52,764
l want all of you
to enjoy your cake...

659
01:23:52,876 --> 01:23:54,764
so enjoy.

660
01:23:54,878 --> 01:23:56,766
- Happy birthday.
- Happy birthday.

661
01:23:58,615 --> 01:24:02,574
l saw an interesting thing
happen today.

662
01:24:02,686 --> 01:24:05,814
A rebel was being arrested
by the military police...

663
01:24:05,922 --> 01:24:07,685
and rather than be taken alive...

664
01:24:07,791 --> 01:24:10,419
he exploded a grenade he had
hidden in his jacket.

665
01:24:10,527 --> 01:24:13,917
He killed himself, and he took
a captain of the command with him.

666
01:24:14,030 --> 01:24:16,225
- Right,Johnny?
- Those rebels, they're lunatics.

667
01:24:16,333 --> 01:24:19,598
- Yes, l agree.
- Maybe so.

668
01:24:19,703 --> 01:24:21,295
But it occurred to me...

669
01:24:21,404 --> 01:24:24,737
the soldiers are paid to fight,
the rebels aren't.

670
01:24:24,841 --> 01:24:27,002
What does that tell you?

671
01:24:27,110 --> 01:24:28,998
They could win.

672
01:24:30,847 --> 01:24:33,645
This country has had rebels
for the last 50 years.

673
01:24:33,750 --> 01:24:38,380
lt's in their blood. l've been
coming here since the '20s.

674
01:24:38,488 --> 01:24:42,310
We were running molasses out
of Havana when you were a baby...

675
01:24:42,425 --> 01:24:46,020
the trucks owned by your father.

676
01:24:46,129 --> 01:24:48,620
Michael.

677
01:24:54,704 --> 01:24:57,593
l'd rather we talked about
this when we we're alone.

678
01:25:00,543 --> 01:25:03,432
The two million
never got to the island.

679
01:25:09,286 --> 01:25:12,414
l wouldn't want it to get around
that you held back the money...

680
01:25:12,522 --> 01:25:15,878
because you had second thoughts
about the rebels.

681
01:25:21,264 --> 01:25:24,188
Ah, sit down, Michael.

682
01:25:24,301 --> 01:25:26,189
Sit down.

683
01:25:32,676 --> 01:25:36,498
lf l could only live to see it,
to be there with you.

684
01:25:36,613 --> 01:25:38,945
Ohh.

685
01:25:39,049 --> 01:25:41,540
What l wouldn't give for...

686
01:25:41,618 --> 01:25:43,506
20 more years.

687
01:25:45,088 --> 01:25:47,613
Here we are, protected--

688
01:25:47,724 --> 01:25:49,783
free to make our profits without
Kefauver...

689
01:25:49,893 --> 01:25:53,590
the goddamn Justice
Department and the FBl--

690
01:25:53,697 --> 01:25:57,224
90 miles away, partnership
with a friendly government.

691
01:25:58,668 --> 01:26:02,866
Ninety miles. lt's nothing.

692
01:26:02,973 --> 01:26:05,533
Just one small step,
looking for a man...

693
01:26:05,642 --> 01:26:08,805
that wants to be President
of the United States...

694
01:26:08,912 --> 01:26:12,268
and having the cash
to make it possible.

695
01:26:12,382 --> 01:26:14,270
Michael...

696
01:26:15,885 --> 01:26:18,740
we're bigger than U.S. Steel.

697
01:26:44,914 --> 01:26:47,303
Mikey, how are ya? Okay?

698
01:26:49,352 --> 01:26:52,082
Hiya. Freddie Corleone.

699
01:26:55,291 --> 01:26:57,555
Jesus Christ, what a trip.

700
01:26:57,660 --> 01:26:59,093
The whole time l'm thinkin'...

701
01:26:59,195 --> 01:27:01,288
''What if somebody knows
what l got in here?''

702
01:27:01,398 --> 01:27:05,721
lmagine that. Two million dollars
on the seat next to me.

703
01:27:05,835 --> 01:27:07,723
All right.

704
01:27:09,305 --> 01:27:11,694
- Whoops. Excuse me.
- No, it's okay.

705
01:27:14,010 --> 01:27:15,898
You wanna count it?

706
01:27:20,350 --> 01:27:23,808
Mikey, what the hell's
goin' on anyway?

707
01:27:23,920 --> 01:27:26,150
The family's making
an investment in Havana.

708
01:27:26,256 --> 01:27:29,589
- This is a gift for the president.
- Oh.

709
01:27:29,692 --> 01:27:31,648
Well, that's great.

710
01:27:31,761 --> 01:27:33,649
Havana's great.

711
01:27:34,764 --> 01:27:36,652
lt's my kind of town.

712
01:27:38,201 --> 01:27:40,294
- Anybody l know in Havana?
- l don't know.

713
01:27:40,403 --> 01:27:42,359
Hyman Roth? Johnny Ola?

714
01:27:45,842 --> 01:27:48,367
No. l never met them.

715
01:27:52,148 --> 01:27:54,446
Listen, Mikey...

716
01:27:54,551 --> 01:27:56,439
l'm kind of, uh--

717
01:27:59,989 --> 01:28:01,388
kind of nervous from the trip.

718
01:28:01,491 --> 01:28:05,120
Uh, can l-- can l get
a, uh, drink or somethin'?

719
01:28:05,228 --> 01:28:08,493
l thought maybe we'd--
we'd go out together.

720
01:28:08,598 --> 01:28:11,487
l know a place we can spend
some time together. Okay?

721
01:28:14,003 --> 01:28:17,166
Sometimes l think l should've
married a woman like you did...

722
01:28:17,273 --> 01:28:19,662
like Kay.

723
01:28:19,776 --> 01:28:22,165
Have kids, have a family.

724
01:28:24,848 --> 01:28:28,238
For once in my life
be more like...

725
01:28:29,652 --> 01:28:31,244
Pop.

726
01:28:33,490 --> 01:28:38,245
lt's not easy to be a son,
Fredo. lt's not easy.

727
01:28:38,361 --> 01:28:41,489
Mama used to tease me. She'd say,
''You don't belong to me.

728
01:28:41,598 --> 01:28:45,125
You were left on the doorstep
by gypsies.''

729
01:28:45,235 --> 01:28:48,090
Sometimes l think it's true.

730
01:28:48,204 --> 01:28:50,092
You're no gypsy, Fredo.

731
01:28:51,741 --> 01:28:53,732
Mikey, l--

732
01:28:53,843 --> 01:28:55,731
l was mad at you.

733
01:29:02,986 --> 01:29:06,911
Why didn't we spend time
like this before?

734
01:29:07,023 --> 01:29:09,412
You want a drink, right?
Waiter.

735
01:29:17,233 --> 01:29:20,088
- How do you say banana daiquiri?
- Banana daiquiri.

736
01:29:20,203 --> 01:29:22,467
- That's it?
- That's it.

737
01:29:22,572 --> 01:29:25,461
- Uh, uno banana daiquiri.
- Banana daiquiri. Si, senor.

738
01:29:25,575 --> 01:29:27,964
And, uh, a club soda.

739
01:29:35,818 --> 01:29:38,616
Senator Geary's flying in
from Washington tomorrow night...

740
01:29:38,721 --> 01:29:41,110
with some people,
some government people...

741
