02:22:58,951 --> 02:23:01,249
of the most powerful Mafia family
in this country.

978
02:23:01,354 --> 02:23:04,243
- Are you?
- No, I'm not.

979
02:23:04,357 --> 02:23:07,849
The witness has testified that
you are personally responsible...

980
02:23:07,960 --> 02:23:11,589
for the murder of a New York City
police captain in 1 94 7.

981
02:23:11,697 --> 02:23:15,428
And with him,
a man named Virgil Solozzo.

982
02:23:15,535 --> 02:23:17,799
- Do you deny this?
- Yes, l do.

983
02:23:17,904 --> 02:23:21,169
ls it true that in the year 1 950...

984
02:23:21,274 --> 02:23:25,631
you devised a murder of the heads
of the so-called ''five families''...

985
02:23:25,745 --> 02:23:28,043
in New York, to assume
and consolidate...

986
02:23:28,147 --> 02:23:30,536
your nefarious power?

987
02:23:30,650 --> 02:23:34,472
- That's a complete falsehood.
- Is it true...

988
02:23:34,587 --> 02:23:38,444
you have a controlling interest
in three major hotels in Las Vegas?

989
02:23:39,725 --> 02:23:43,354
No, it is not true. l own some stock
in some of the hotels there...

990
02:23:43,462 --> 02:23:45,521
but very little.

991
02:23:47,700 --> 02:23:51,796
l also have stock in lBM and lT&T.

992
02:23:51,904 --> 02:23:57,262
Do you have any interests or control
over gambling and narcotics...

993
02:23:57,376 --> 02:23:58,866
in the state of New York?

994
02:23:58,945 --> 02:24:00,867
No, l do not.

995
02:24:00,980 --> 02:24:04,143
Senator, my client would like to
read a statement for this committee.

996
02:24:04,250 --> 02:24:08,038
Mr. Chairman,
l think this statement...

997
02:24:08,154 --> 02:24:10,349
is totally out of order
at this time.

998
02:24:10,456 --> 02:24:14,244
Sir, my client has answered every
question asked by this committee...

999
02:24:14,360 --> 02:24:16,123
with the utmost sincerity.

1000
02:24:16,228 --> 02:24:19,152
He did not take the Fifth Amendment,
as it was his right to do...

1001
02:24:19,265 --> 02:24:21,927
so in all fairness l think
the statement should be heard.

1002
02:24:24,203 --> 02:24:27,366
No, l'm going to allow Mr. Corleone
to read his statement.

1003
02:24:27,473 --> 02:24:28,872
l'll put it in the record.

1004
02:24:30,876 --> 02:24:34,004
''ln the hopes of clearing
my family name...

1005
02:24:34,113 --> 02:24:36,673
and my sincere desire to give
my children their fair share...

1006
02:24:36,782 --> 02:24:38,841
of the American way of life
without a blemish...

1007
02:24:38,951 --> 02:24:41,283
on their name and background...

1008
02:24:41,387 --> 02:24:43,412
l have appeared
before this committee...

1009
02:24:43,522 --> 02:24:46,411
and given it all the cooperation
in my power.

1010
02:24:47,793 --> 02:24:50,751
l consider it a great dishonor
to me personally...

1011
02:24:50,863 --> 02:24:53,252
to have to deny
that l am a criminal.

1012
02:24:54,200 --> 02:24:57,863
l wish to have the following
noted for the record:

1013
02:24:57,970 --> 02:25:01,997
that l served my country faithfully
and honorably in World War Two...

1014
02:25:02,108 --> 02:25:06,499
and was awarded a Navy Cross for
actions in defense of my country...

1015
02:25:08,080 --> 02:25:12,471
that l have never been arrested or
indicted for any crime whatsoever...

1016
02:25:12,585 --> 02:25:16,646
that no proof linking me to any
criminal conspiracy...

1017
02:25:16,756 --> 02:25:19,384
whether it is called ''Mafia,''
''Cosa Nostra''...

1018
02:25:19,492 --> 02:25:21,380
or whatever other name
you wish to give...

1019
02:25:21,494 --> 02:25:22,893
has ever been made public.

1020
02:25:24,163 --> 02:25:26,996
I have not taken refuge
behind the Fifth Amendment...

1021
02:25:27,099 --> 02:25:29,158
although it is my right to do so.

1022
02:25:32,204 --> 02:25:34,195
l challenge this committee...

1023
02:25:34,306 --> 02:25:37,764
to produce any witness
or evidence against me.

1024
02:25:37,877 --> 02:25:40,300
And if they do not...

1025
02:25:40,413 --> 02:25:43,871
l hope they will have the decency
to clear my name...

1026
02:25:43,983 --> 02:25:47,282
with the same publicity with which
they now have besmirched it.''

1027
02:25:48,954 --> 02:25:51,980
I'm sure we're all quite impressed,
Mr. Corleone...

1028
02:25:52,091 --> 02:25:54,582
particularly with your love
for our country.

1029
02:25:54,660 --> 02:25:57,356
Committee will stand in recess
until 1 0:00 a.m. Monday morning...

1030
02:25:57,463 --> 02:25:59,351
at which time the committee
will produce a witness...

1031
02:25:59,465 --> 02:26:02,195
who will corroborate the charges
which were made against you today...

1032
02:26:02,301 --> 02:26:05,293
and at which time, Mr. Corleone,
you may very well be subject...

1033
02:26:05,404 --> 02:26:07,463
to indictment for perjury.

1034
02:26:07,573 --> 02:26:09,700
l remind you that
you're still under subpoena.

1035
02:26:09,809 --> 02:26:11,697
Adjourned.

1036
02:26:15,915 --> 02:26:18,713
Ten-to-one shot, you said.

1037
02:26:18,818 --> 02:26:21,776
Ten-to-one shot
he would take the Fifth...

1038
02:26:21,887 --> 02:26:23,616
and l lose.

1039
02:26:23,723 --> 02:26:25,714
You sound like my bookie.

1040
02:26:25,825 --> 02:26:27,884
l owe that monkey my life.

1041
02:26:29,695 --> 02:26:31,720
Well, just get
a good night's sleep.

1042
02:26:31,831 --> 02:26:35,221
- Good night's sleep.
- Got a big day tomorrow.

1043
02:26:35,334 --> 02:26:38,258
Got you a new suit,
a new shirt, new tie.

1044
02:26:39,872 --> 02:26:42,261
l'm gonna shave you myself
in the morning.

1045
02:26:43,209 --> 02:26:47,168
You're gonna look respectable for
50 million of your fellow Americans.

1046
02:26:48,614 --> 02:26:53,506
My life won't be worth a nickel
after tomorrow.

1047
02:26:53,619 --> 02:26:57,009
Come on.
l saw this thing 1 9 times.

1048
02:26:58,390 --> 02:27:00,915
You got a great home here, Frankie.

1049
02:27:01,026 --> 02:27:04,985
The rest of your life, nobody gets
near you, you're not going anywhere.

1050
02:27:05,097 --> 02:27:08,328
That's great.
Beautiful.

1051
02:27:08,434 --> 02:27:10,390
Some deal l made.

1052
02:27:10,503 --> 02:27:13,267
You'll live like a king.
You'll be a hero.

1053
02:27:13,372 --> 02:27:16,432
You'll live better in here
than most people on the outside.

1054
02:27:16,542 --> 02:27:19,340
Some deal.
Jesus.

1055
02:27:21,113 --> 02:27:25,004
Alive.
Pentangeli is alive.

1056
02:27:26,886 --> 02:27:32,017
- How'd they get their hands on him?
- Roth. He engineered it.

1057
02:27:32,792 --> 02:27:35,215
Frankie went to make a deal
with the Rosato brothers...

1058
02:27:35,327 --> 02:27:37,420
and they tried to kill him.

1059
02:27:37,530 --> 02:27:39,418
He thought you double-crossed him.

1060
02:27:41,066 --> 02:27:43,330
Our people with the New York
detective said he was half dead...

1061
02:27:43,435 --> 02:27:47,132
scared stiff and calling out loud
that you turned on him.

1062
02:27:47,239 --> 02:27:49,969
They already had him on possession,
bookmaking, murder one...

1063
02:27:50,075 --> 02:27:51,963
and a lot more.

1064
02:27:53,479 --> 02:27:56,175
The FBl has him airtight.

1065
02:27:56,282 --> 02:27:59,137
He's on an army base,
24-hour guards.

1066
02:27:59,251 --> 02:28:01,446
No way we can get to him.

1067
02:28:01,554 --> 02:28:04,512
You've opened yourself
to five counts of perjury.

1068
02:28:06,725 --> 02:28:09,649
What about Fredo?
What does he know?

1069
02:28:09,762 --> 02:28:12,458
He says he doesn't know anything,
and l believe him.

1070
02:28:13,399 --> 02:28:17,290
Roth-- he played this one
beautifully.

1071
02:28:25,444 --> 02:28:27,332
l want to talk to Fredo.

1072
02:29:07,086 --> 02:29:08,974
l haven't got a lot to say, Mike.

1073
02:29:11,523 --> 02:29:14,014
We have time.

1074
02:29:14,126 --> 02:29:17,015
l was kept pretty much in the dark.

1075
02:29:18,697 --> 02:29:20,585
l didn't know all that much.

1076
02:29:21,867 --> 02:29:26,361
What about now? ls there anything
you can help me out with?

1077
02:29:27,172 --> 02:29:29,060
Anything you can tell me now?

1078
02:29:31,410 --> 02:29:33,799
They got Pentangeli,
that's all l can tell you.

1079
02:29:48,727 --> 02:29:52,254
l didn't know
it was gonna be a hit, Mike.

1080
02:29:52,364 --> 02:29:54,662
l swear to God,
l didn't know it was gonna be a hit.

1081
02:29:57,703 --> 02:30:02,094
Johnny Ola bumped into me
in Beverly Hills...

1082
02:30:03,842 --> 02:30:06,231
and he said
that he wanted to talk.

1083
02:30:08,547 --> 02:30:11,311
He said that you and Roth...

1084
02:30:11,417 --> 02:30:14,807
were in on a big deal together...

1085
02:30:17,189 --> 02:30:21,421
and that there was something in it
for me if l could help him out.

1086
02:30:21,527 --> 02:30:25,349
He said that you were being tough
on the negotiations.

1087
02:30:25,464 --> 02:30:29,855
But if they could get a little help
and close the deal fast...

1088
02:30:31,637 --> 02:30:33,867
it'd be good for the family.

1089
02:30:35,641 --> 02:30:37,700
You believed that story?

1090
02:30:37,810 --> 02:30:40,176
You believed that?

1091
02:30:40,279 --> 02:30:43,942
He said there was something in it
for me... on my own.

1092
02:30:44,049 --> 02:30:46,677
l've always taken care of you.

1093
02:30:46,785 --> 02:30:48,673
Taken care of me?

1094
02:30:49,788 --> 02:30:53,554
You're my kid brother.
You take care of me?

1095
02:30:53,659 --> 02:30:58,790
Did you ever think about that?
Did you ever once think about that?

1096
02:30:58,897 --> 02:31:02,287
Send Fredo off to do this,
send Fredo off to do that.

1097
02:31:03,736 --> 02:31:07,968
Let Fredo take care of some
Mickey Mouse nightclub somewhere.

1098
02:31:08,073 --> 02:31:10,962
Send Fredo to pick somebody up
at the airport.

1099
02:31:11,076 --> 02:31:14,375
l'm your older brother, Mike,
and l was stepped over!

1100
02:31:14,480 --> 02:31:19,235
- That's the way Pop wanted it.
- lt ain't the way l wanted it!

1101
02:31:19,351 --> 02:31:21,842
l can handle things!
l'm smart!

1102
02:31:21,954 --> 02:31:25,913
Not like everybody says.
Like dumb. l'm smart...

1103
02:31:26,025 --> 02:31:28,084
and l want respect!

1104
02:31:36,001 --> 02:31:39,164
ls there anything you can tell me
about this investigation?

1105
02:31:39,271 --> 02:31:41,159
Anything more?

1106
02:31:49,214 --> 02:31:53,310
The Senate lawyer, Questadt...

1107
02:31:53,419 --> 02:31:54,977
he belongs to Roth.

1108
02:32:09,101 --> 02:32:11,160
You're nothing to me now.

1109
02:32:13,605 --> 02:32:15,800
You're not a brother,
you're not a friend.

1110
02:32:17,843 --> 02:32:20,641
l don't wanna know you
or what you do.

1111
02:32:21,814 --> 02:32:24,942
l don't wanna see you at the hotels.

1112
02:32:25,050 --> 02:32:27,439
l don't want you near my house.

1113
02:32:29,588 --> 02:32:32,443
When you see our mother,
l wanna know a day in advance...

1114
02:32:32,558 --> 02:32:34,048
so l won't be there.

1115
02:32:35,961 --> 02:32:38,691
You understand?

1116
02:32:55,781 --> 02:32:59,638
l don't want anything to happen
to him while my mother's alive.

1117
02:33:49,568 --> 02:33:53,197
There are more people
than a ball game in here.

1118
02:33:53,305 --> 02:33:55,193
There's Willi Cicci.

1119
02:34:17,262 --> 02:34:19,150
This committee will come to order.

1120
02:34:22,167 --> 02:34:24,829
- State your name, please.
- Frank Pentangeli.

1121
02:34:24,937 --> 02:34:28,634
- And where were you born?
- Partanego. Outside of Palermo.

1122
02:34:28,740 --> 02:34:30,970
Where do you live now?

1123
02:34:31,076 --> 02:34:35,467
l live in an army barracks
with the FBl guys.

1124
02:34:36,582 --> 02:34:41,747
We have here, finally, a witness
that will further testify...

1125
02:34:41,853 --> 02:34:44,549
to Michael Corleone's rule
over a criminal empire...

1126
02:34:44,656 --> 02:34:46,681
that controls all of the gambling
in this country...

1127
02:34:46,792 --> 02:34:48,191
and perhaps in other countries.

1128
02:34:48,293 --> 02:34:53,549
This witness had no buffer between
himself and Michael Corleone.

1129
02:34:53,665 --> 02:34:57,226
He can corroborate our charges on
enough counts for this committee...

1130
02:34:57,336 --> 02:35:01,693
to recommend a charge of perjury
against Michael Corleone.

1131
02:35:01,807 --> 02:35:03,502
- Senator.
- Thank you, Mr. Chairman.

1132
02:35:05,010 --> 02:35:06,238
Mr. Pentangeli.

1133
02:35:10,449 --> 02:35:13,577
Were you a member
of the Corleone family?

1134
02:35:13,685 --> 02:35:18,247
Did you serve under
caporegime Peter Clemenza...

1135
02:35:18,357 --> 02:35:23,021
under Vito Corleone,
also known as the ''Godfather''?

1136
02:35:29,368 --> 02:35:31,495
l never knew no Godfather.

1137
02:35:34,273 --> 02:35:36,161
l have my own family, Senator.

1138
02:35:40,145 --> 02:35:44,411
Mr. Pentangeli, you are
contradicting a sworn statement...

1139
02:35:44,516 --> 02:35:46,404
you'd previously made to me
and signed.

1140
02:35:46,518 --> 02:35:50,079
l ask you again, sir,
here and now under oath...

1141
02:35:50,188 --> 02:35:54,716
were you at any time
a member of a crime organization...

1142
02:35:54,826 --> 02:35:56,225
headed by Michael Corleone?

1143
02:35:56,328 --> 02:36:00,025
l don't know nothing about that.

1144
02:36:03,101 --> 02:36:07,026
l was in the olive oil business
with his father...

1145
02:36:07,139 --> 02:36:09,528
but that was a long time ago,
that's all.

1146
02:36:10,676 --> 02:36:12,564
We have a sworn affidavit.

1147
02:36:14,079 --> 02:36:17,173
We have it--
your sworn affidavit...

1148
02:36:17,282 --> 02:36:19,773
that you murdered on
the orders of Michael Corleone.

1149
02:36:19,885 --> 02:36:22,046
Do you deny that confession?

1150
02:36:22,154 --> 02:36:24,918
And do you realize what will happen
as a result of your denial?

1151
02:36:25,023 --> 02:36:28,151
Look, the FBl guys,
they promised me a deal...

1152
02:36:28,260 --> 02:36:31,991
so l made up a lot of stuff
about Michael Corleone...

1153
02:36:32,097 --> 02:36:34,053
'cause that's what they wanted.

1154
02:36:34,166 --> 02:36:37,988
But it was all lies--
everything.

1155
02:36:38,937 --> 02:36:41,303
And they kept saying...

1156
02:36:41,406 --> 02:36:43,567
Michael Corleone did this...

1157
02:36:43,675 --> 02:36:46,235
and that Michael Corleone did that.

1158
02:36:47,679 --> 02:36:51,775
So l said, ''Yeah, sure!''

1159
02:36:51,883 --> 02:36:55,478
Mr. Corleone, would you kindly
identify for the committee...

1160
02:36:55,587 --> 02:36:57,475
the gentleman sitting
to your left?

1161
02:36:57,589 --> 02:36:59,477
l can answer that.

1162
02:37:00,792 --> 02:37:03,784
His name is Vincenzo Pentangeli.

1163
02:37:03,895 --> 02:37:07,991
- Is he related to the witness?
- He is, l believe, his brother.

1164
02:37:08,100 --> 02:37:10,591
Will he come forward
and be sworn, sir?

1165
02:37:10,702 --> 02:37:13,398
Sir, this man
does not understand English.

1166
02:37:13,505 --> 02:37:17,134
He came at his own expense to aid
his brother in this time of trouble.

1167
02:37:17,242 --> 02:37:20,905
He's not under subpoena.
His reputation is impeccable.

1168
02:37:21,012 --> 02:37:22,877
Are you saying he knows nothing
about these matters?

1169
02:37:22,981 --> 02:37:24,380
To my knowledge, nothing.

1170
02:37:24,483 --> 02:37:27,441
l'm gonna find out
what the hell happened here.

1171
02:37:27,552 --> 02:37:29,543
All right, this committee
is now adjourned.

1172
02:37:29,654 --> 02:37:31,849
- The witness is excused.
- Senator!

1173
02:37:34,226 --> 02:37:37,059
This committee owes an apology!

1174
02:37:37,162 --> 02:37:41,053
This committee owes an apology.
Apology, Senator.

1175
02:38:08,927 --> 02:38:12,556
- Michael, excuse me.
- Hold on a minute.

1176
02:38:12,664 --> 02:38:15,360
The children are outside.
We're going.

1177
02:38:18,203 --> 02:38:20,501
What do you mean you're going?
We're all gonna leave tomorrow.

1178
02:38:25,110 --> 02:38:26,998
l'll be in my room.

1179
02:38:30,415 --> 02:38:33,373
Michael, l'm not going
back to Nevada.

1180
02:38:33,485 --> 02:38:36,374
l brought the children
to say good-bye to you.

1181
02:38:40,258 --> 02:38:42,385
l want you to know
l'm very happy for you.

1182
02:38:42,494 --> 02:38:45,019
l suppose l always knew
you were too smart...

1183
02:38:45,130 --> 02:38:47,052
to let any of them
ever beat you.

1184
02:38:48,934 --> 02:38:53,394
- Why don't you sit down?
- l'm not going to stay long.

1185
02:38:53,505 --> 02:38:55,894
There are some things
l'd like to talk to you about.

1186
02:38:57,676 --> 02:39:00,065
Some things that have been
on my mind.

1187
02:39:01,346 --> 02:39:05,442
- Changes l wanna make.
- l think it's too late for changes.

1188
02:39:06,952 --> 02:39:09,045
l promised myself
l wasn't going to say anything.

1189
02:39:09,154 --> 02:39:12,578
You're too late.

1190
02:39:16,995 --> 02:39:19,384
What really happened
with Pentangeli?

1191
02:39:25,670 --> 02:39:27,695
His brother came, helped him.

1192
02:39:27,806 --> 02:39:30,730
l didn't even know
he had a brother.

1193
02:39:30,842 --> 02:39:32,730
Where is he now?

1194
02:39:33,945 --> 02:39:36,368
He's on a plane back to Sicily.

1195
02:39:37,148 --> 02:39:39,571
All he had to do
was show his face.

1196
02:39:41,520 --> 02:39:46,082
lt was between the brothers.
l had nothing to do with it.

1197
02:39:54,266 --> 02:39:59,363
Nobody is going--
not you, not the kids! You hear me?

1198
02:39:59,471 --> 02:40:03,168
You're my wife, they're my children.
l love you. l won't allow it.

1199
02:40:04,276 --> 02:40:08,133
You say you love me, then you
talk about allowing me to leave!

1200
02:40:08,246 --> 02:40:11,306
Things have been going on for years
between men and women...

1201
02:40:11,416 --> 02:40:13,304
- that will not change.
- You've become blind!

1202
02:40:13,418 --> 02:40:16,307
- Blind to what?
- Look what happened to us.

1203
02:40:16,421 --> 02:40:19,481
- Look what's happened to our son!
- Nothing's happened--

1204
02:40:19,591 --> 02:40:22,754
- Anthony is fine!
- Anthony is not fine!

1205
02:40:22,861 --> 02:40:24,783
- l don't wanna hear about it!
- You will!

1206
02:40:24,896 --> 02:40:27,421
Anthony's not fine!

1207
02:40:27,532 --> 02:40:29,159
l don't wanna hear about it!

1208
02:40:30,068 --> 02:40:31,626
Over!

1209
02:40:44,749 --> 02:40:47,638
At this moment,
l feel no love for you at all.

1210
02:40:49,321 --> 02:40:51,710
l never thought
that would ever happen...

